WEBVTT

00:14.098 --> 00:15.764
(static)
(crickets chirping)

00:15.808 --> 00:17.015
(footsteps)

00:21.313 --> 00:24.148
(girl breathing heavily)
(running footsteps)

00:25.317 --> 00:27.484
(static)

00:33.451 --> 00:35.117
(girl whimpers)

00:37.204 --> 00:39.329
(footsteps stop)
(girl panting)

00:41.917 --> 00:44.126
(static)

00:46.046 --> 00:48.964
Girl:
Hey! Over here!

00:51.719 --> 00:53.093
(static stops)

00:53.137 --> 00:55.220
(girl panting)
(crickets chirping)

00:57.308 --> 00:58.849
(twig snaps)

01:00.227 --> 01:02.978
(girl panting)

01:05.649 --> 01:06.690
Girl:
Please!

01:09.570 --> 01:10.694
(girl grunts)

01:12.406 --> 01:14.364
(feedback)

01:14.408 --> 01:16.784
(static)

01:16.827 --> 01:17.868
(girl screams)

01:23.959 --> 01:25.751
(computer mouse clicks)

01:25.795 --> 01:29.254
(ominous music playing)

02:21.851 --> 02:24.226
(sirens approaching)

02:31.318 --> 02:34.278
♪ ♪

02:35.823 --> 02:38.282
(sirens approaching)

02:52.965 --> 02:55.591
Dispatcher on phone:
<i>911, what is the address</i>
<i>of your emergency?</i>

02:55.634 --> 02:58.427
Officer:<i> Waukesha County,</i>
<i> I'm gonna transfer over</i>
<i> a caller on Big Bend.</i>

02:58.470 --> 03:01.513
<i> That's a dead end</i>
<i> just south of Rivera.</i>

03:01.557 --> 03:04.349
Dispatcher:<i> Okay.</i>
Officer:<i> He came upon</i>
<i> a 12-year-old female.</i>

03:04.393 --> 03:05.893
<i> She appears</i>
<i> to have been stabbed.</i>

03:05.936 --> 03:07.394
Dispatcher:
<i>She appears to be what?</i>

03:07.438 --> 03:08.687
Officer:<i> Stabbed.</i>
Dispatcher:<i> Stabbed?</i>

03:08.731 --> 03:09.813
Officer:
<i> Correct.</i>

03:12.234 --> 03:16.778
On Saturday, May 31st, 2014,
at approximately 9:50 a.m.,

03:16.822 --> 03:18.697
the Waukesha
Police Department
was notified

03:18.741 --> 03:20.282
<i>by a concerned</i>
<i>citizen</i>

03:20.326 --> 03:22.284
<i>that a 12-year-old girl</i>
<i>was stabbed</i>

03:22.328 --> 03:25.746
<i>in the area</i>
<i>of Big Bend Road</i>
<i>in the city of Waukesha.</i>

03:25.789 --> 03:28.916
Female reporter:
<i> The stabbing brought a huge</i>
<i> police presence to the area,</i>

03:28.959 --> 03:33.128
<i> a major search</i>
<i> by ground and air</i>
<i> looking for two other girls.</i>

03:33.172 --> 03:34.755
<i> Anissa Weier</i>
<i> and Morgan Geyser</i>

03:34.798 --> 03:36.590
<i> are accused</i>
<i> of stabbing their friend</i>

03:36.634 --> 03:38.133
<i> and leaving her for dead.</i>

03:38.177 --> 03:41.094
Male reporter:
<i>Weier and Geyser lured Payton</i>
<i> into the woods</i>

03:41.138 --> 03:43.347
Male reporter 2:
<i>Police say that's when Geyser,</i>
<i> holding the knife,</i>

03:43.390 --> 03:46.308
<i> was told by Weier,</i>
<i> "Go ballistic, go crazy."</i>

03:46.352 --> 03:48.644
♪ ♪

03:48.687 --> 03:50.020
Attorney:
And what happened?

03:50.064 --> 03:52.481
Payton said,
"Then she started."

03:52.524 --> 03:54.399
Male reporter 3:
<i> Geyser began to stab</i>
<i> the 12-year-old,</i>

03:54.443 --> 03:57.653
<i> as she screamed, 19 times</i>
<i> with a five-inch blade.</i>

03:57.696 --> 04:00.155
Sheriff:<i> In the arms,</i>
<i> legs, and torso.</i>

04:00.199 --> 04:02.908
Male reporter:
<i> One of the knife wounds</i>
<i> missed a major artery</i>

04:02.952 --> 04:05.452
<i> near her heart</i>
<i> by just a millimeter.</i>

04:05.496 --> 04:07.829
♪ ♪

04:07.873 --> 04:09.331
Female reporter 2:
<i> Payton somehow survived.</i>

04:09.375 --> 04:10.958
<i> She crawled out</i>
<i> of those woods.</i>

04:11.001 --> 04:13.293
Female reporter 3:
<i> A bicyclist found her</i>
<i> on the sidewalk,</i>

04:13.337 --> 04:15.587
<i> covered in blood</i>
<i> and begging for help.</i>

04:15.631 --> 04:19.174
<i> When asked who attacked her,</i>
<i> she said, "My best friend."</i>

04:20.844 --> 04:23.220
Police say the suspects
were inspired by a character

04:23.263 --> 04:25.180
on a website
called Creepypasta,

04:25.224 --> 04:27.057
<i> a site filled</i>
<i> with scary stories.</i>

04:27.101 --> 04:28.517
<i> Now, the story they followed</i>

04:28.560 --> 04:30.852
<i> was about a character</i>
<i> called Slenderman.</i>

04:30.896 --> 04:34.606
A tall, fictional boogeyman
featured on Internet blogs.

04:34.650 --> 04:36.525
Slenderman, a faceless ghoul

04:36.568 --> 04:38.443
many parents have likely
never heard of.

04:38.487 --> 04:40.362
Female reporter 4:
<i> If you don't know</i>
<i> who Slenderman is--</i>

04:40.406 --> 04:43.448
well, we didn't either,
but plenty of young kids do.

04:43.492 --> 04:45.367
If you don't know
who Slenderman is,
you live under a rock.

04:45.411 --> 04:46.493
Who's that?

04:46.537 --> 04:49.579
(static)
(boy yelling)
Run! Run! Run!

04:49.623 --> 04:51.331
Oh my god, run! No, run!

04:51.375 --> 04:54.167
Boy 2:
Oh my god!
Girl: Oh my god!

04:54.211 --> 04:56.211
Male reporter 2:
<i>Anissa Weier and Morgan Geyser</i>

04:56.255 --> 04:58.255
<i> were found walking</i>
<i> near the interstate.</i>

04:58.298 --> 05:00.257
<i> They later told police</i>
<i> they planned to walk</i>

05:00.300 --> 05:02.009
<i> to Slenderman's mansion.</i>

05:02.052 --> 05:03.510
Female reporter 5:
<i>Police say it's also who</i>

05:03.554 --> 05:06.263
<i>the young suspects claimed</i>
<i>they wanted to please.</i>

05:06.306 --> 05:09.516
Detective Trussoni:
<i> Anissa felt as though</i>
<i> she needed to prove</i>

05:09.560 --> 05:12.894
that Slenderman existed
and would be able to do that
by killing somebody.

05:12.938 --> 05:16.732
And Morgan said
that her family would be
in danger if they didn't.

05:16.775 --> 05:19.192
Prosecutors have charged
the girls as adults.

05:19.236 --> 05:20.610
If convicted on the charges,

05:20.654 --> 05:22.529
each 12-year-old faces

05:22.573 --> 05:25.824
<i> up to 65 years in prison.</i>

05:25.868 --> 05:29.453
(static)

05:35.711 --> 05:37.461
(Morgan speaks
matter-of-factly)

05:38.672 --> 05:39.796
(Detective Casey speaks)

05:40.799 --> 05:42.090
(Morgan speaks)

05:45.304 --> 05:47.971
♪ ♪

05:50.142 --> 05:52.350
<i> (Detective Trussoni</i>
<i> speaking on video)</i>

06:00.778 --> 06:02.152
(crying)

06:28.931 --> 06:30.722
<i> (Casey speaks</i>
<i> matter-of-factly)</i>

06:30.766 --> 06:32.182
<i>(Morgan speaks</i>
<i>on video)</i>

06:33.727 --> 06:35.685
<i> (Casey speaks)</i>

06:35.729 --> 06:37.687
<i>(Morgan speaks)</i>

06:37.731 --> 06:39.689
<i> (Casey speaks)</i>

06:39.733 --> 06:41.817
(Morgan speaking)

06:51.495 --> 06:54.579
♪ ♪

06:57.835 --> 07:00.961
Attorney:<i> Did it seem</i>
<i>to you at any point during</i>
<i>your interview with Morgan</i>

07:01.004 --> 07:03.213
that she was remorseful
about what she had done?

07:03.257 --> 07:05.966
Absolutely none.

07:06.009 --> 07:08.927
Attorney:
Did she cry at all at any point
during your interview of her?

07:08.971 --> 07:10.846
There was no emotion
from her at all.

07:10.889 --> 07:12.556
♪ ♪

07:18.313 --> 07:21.565
Attorney:
<i>Did you, after discussing</i>
<i>the incident itself,</i>

07:21.608 --> 07:23.775
<i>have any conversation</i>
<i>with Payton</i>

07:23.819 --> 07:27.487
about how she felt
about Morgan and Anissa
at this point?

07:27.531 --> 07:33.410
She said
that Morgan should go to jail
for the rest of her life...

07:33.453 --> 07:37.581
and that Anissa should
go to jail too, but not as long

07:37.624 --> 07:40.834
because she was involved
but she didn't stab her.

07:40.878 --> 07:42.210
She just stood there
and watched.

07:42.254 --> 07:43.962
♪ ♪

07:52.890 --> 07:54.264
Angie Geyser on video:
<i> Hi, Morgan.</i>

07:54.308 --> 07:57.642
(babbles)
Angie:
Hi, Morgan.

08:03.108 --> 08:04.274
(discordant notes)

08:07.696 --> 08:11.448
Angie:
<i> Morgan was a surprise.</i>

08:11.491 --> 08:16.578
And I didn't know how to feel
about it at first...

08:17.664 --> 08:20.790
<i> but I knew that I loved her.</i>

08:23.629 --> 08:24.920
Yay!

08:24.963 --> 08:28.965
Angie:
<i> And she changed</i>
<i> our lives drastically</i>

08:29.009 --> 08:30.425
<i> and for the better.</i>

08:30.469 --> 08:32.886
(babbles)

08:32.930 --> 08:34.763
Angie:
<i> Morgan's always been quirky,</i>

08:34.806 --> 08:37.515
<i> and she's always marched</i>
<i> to the beat of her own drum.</i>

08:40.312 --> 08:43.772
<i> Even from--</i>
<i> from little on...</i>

08:43.815 --> 08:47.192
she didn't care
what people think about her,

08:47.236 --> 08:52.530
which I think is
a wonderful trait,
especially for-- for a girl.

08:52.574 --> 08:54.532
Girls are usually so--

08:54.576 --> 08:56.785
so self-conscious
and concerned about--

08:56.828 --> 09:00.538
about what others think of them,
and Morgan was never like that.

09:00.582 --> 09:03.333
You know, she just...
(sighs)

09:03.377 --> 09:05.418
She always just did
her own thing,

09:05.462 --> 09:07.420
and if people didn't like it,

09:07.464 --> 09:10.048
well, that was
their problem.
(chuckles)

09:10.092 --> 09:14.928
Kitties and puppies
aren't wild animals.

09:14.972 --> 09:17.764
Angie:
No, that's right.
They're not. They're pets.

09:17.808 --> 09:19.391
Angie:
<i> I had a camera in her face</i>

09:19.434 --> 09:21.518
<i> for a good portion</i>
<i> of her childhood,</i>

09:21.561 --> 09:24.688
<i> so I think she got sick</i>
<i> of it sometimes.</i>
(mimics meowing)

09:29.444 --> 09:34.114
<i> She got a real</i>
<i> miniature baby grand piano</i>
<i> for Christmas one year.</i>

09:34.157 --> 09:36.783
(playing music, singing)
<i> And she would sit there</i>
<i> for quite a long time,</i>

09:36.827 --> 09:39.911
<i> just making up</i>
<i> sweet little songs.</i>

09:39.955 --> 09:42.706
<i> And we tried</i>
<i> to capture as many of them</i>
<i> as we could on video,</i>

09:42.749 --> 09:46.084
<i> but usually as soon</i>
<i> as she realized that</i>
<i> we were paying attention</i>

09:46.128 --> 09:49.087
<i> or recording her,</i>
<i> she would stop.</i>
<i> (chuckles)</i>

09:49.131 --> 09:53.758
♪ They'll stay stray forever ♪

09:54.761 --> 09:56.011
(crying, sniffles)

09:56.054 --> 09:59.931
One thing about Morgan
that always struck us...

09:59.975 --> 10:04.436
as a little...
odd was that she...

10:05.605 --> 10:08.148
(sighs)
She didn't react the way

10:08.191 --> 10:11.943
that you would
expect her to react...

10:11.987 --> 10:14.571
like at the movies.

10:14.614 --> 10:20.285
Like, if something bad happened
to the main character, she...

10:21.413 --> 10:23.330
she wouldn't
have empathy for them.

10:23.373 --> 10:24.956
♪ ♪
Bambi, come here!

10:26.543 --> 10:27.917
Look.

10:27.961 --> 10:30.628
New spring grass.

10:30.672 --> 10:34.883
Angie:
<i> I remember watching "Bambi"</i>
<i> with her for the first time.</i>

10:34.926 --> 10:37.218
We were so worried
to watch it with her,

10:37.262 --> 10:41.139
because we thought
she was gonna be so upset
when-- when the mother died.

10:41.183 --> 10:45.226
♪ ♪
Bambi, quick! The thicket!

10:48.315 --> 10:49.439
(gunshot)

10:50.817 --> 10:53.610
Faster! Faster, Bambi!

10:53.653 --> 10:58.782
Don't look back!
Keep running! Keep running!

11:01.745 --> 11:03.536
(gunshot)

11:03.580 --> 11:06.623
But the mother died,
and Morgan just said,

11:06.666 --> 11:09.626
"Run Bambi, run!
Get out of there,
save yourself!"

11:09.669 --> 11:12.504
<i> (laughs) You know?</i>
<i> And she wasn't sad about it.</i>

11:12.547 --> 11:14.964
♪ ♪
(panting)
We made it!

11:16.218 --> 11:17.801
We made it, Mother!

11:18.804 --> 11:19.844
We...

11:20.806 --> 11:21.971
Mother!

11:25.102 --> 11:27.894
And I could think of...
(sniffles)

11:27.938 --> 11:31.564
a lot of other examples
along those lines

11:31.608 --> 11:33.608
where she hasn't reacted
in the way

11:33.652 --> 11:36.820
that we would expect
a little girl to react.

11:36.863 --> 11:39.781
♪ ♪
(static)

11:47.791 --> 11:51.751
Angie:
<i> We were aware that Morgan</i>
<i>was interested in Slenderman.</i>

11:51.795 --> 11:54.546
(distorted scream)
(static)

11:54.589 --> 11:58.550
<i> She would show us</i>
<i> some of the characters</i>
<i> and some of the stories.</i>

12:00.720 --> 12:03.096
<i> While I wasn't thrilled</i>
<i> about her interest,</i>

12:03.140 --> 12:05.014
<i> I didn't really see</i>
<i> the harm in it either.</i>

12:06.768 --> 12:10.478
We never thought
for a moment that she...

12:11.731 --> 12:16.067
She could possibly believe
that it was real.

12:16.111 --> 12:18.736
When I was
Morgan's age, I--

12:18.780 --> 12:23.408
I remember
biking home from the library
with Stephen King's "It."

12:23.452 --> 12:27.162
You know, so I liked
that sort of thing too
when I was her age,

12:27.205 --> 12:32.375
and I think most kids
her age do like scary stories
and horror movies and...

12:32.419 --> 12:36.463
scary stories
on the Internet, you know?
So, that's all that we--

12:36.506 --> 12:38.381
that's all that
we thought that it was.

12:40.260 --> 12:42.886
I just can't imagine her...

12:42.929 --> 12:46.598
I can't imagine her coming up
with that plan on her own.

12:48.602 --> 12:51.269
♪ My bonnie... ♪

12:52.355 --> 12:57.567
♪ My bonnie lies
over the ocean ♪

12:57.611 --> 13:02.614
♪ My bonnie
lies over the sea ♪

13:02.657 --> 13:07.327
♪ My bonnie lies
over the ocean ♪

13:07.370 --> 13:11.873
♪ So bring back
my bonnie to me ♪

13:11.917 --> 13:13.625
(birds chirping)

13:13.668 --> 13:18.379
♪ Bring back, bring back ♪

13:18.423 --> 13:22.717
♪ Oh, bring back
my bonnie to me ♪

13:24.304 --> 13:26.054
♪ Bring back! ♪

13:26.932 --> 13:28.932
♪ Bring back ♪
♪ Back ♪

13:28.975 --> 13:34.771
♪ Oh, bring back
my bonnie to me ♪
♪ Bonnie... me ♪

13:34.814 --> 13:36.731
(mouse clicking)

13:43.490 --> 13:46.366
Bill Weier:<i> She lost</i>
<i>a tooth, so the tooth fairy</i>
<i>gave her a dollar.</i>

13:46.409 --> 13:48.409
It was that tooth.

13:48.453 --> 13:50.286
I was telling her--
I was like, "A dollar?"

13:50.330 --> 13:52.413
I said,
"I only ever got quarters
from the tooth fairy."

13:53.500 --> 13:55.708
(chuckles)
She was happy.

13:55.752 --> 13:57.126
The tooth fairy
gave her a dollar.

14:00.590 --> 14:01.756
(mouse clicks)

14:01.800 --> 14:04.717
This was
the last video
I have.

14:04.761 --> 14:08.972
This was at the end of her
sixth grade year for school.

14:09.015 --> 14:13.059
Choir:
♪ Hush, hush,
somebody's callin' my name ♪

14:13.103 --> 14:17.313
♪ Hush! Somebody's
callin' my name ♪

14:17.357 --> 14:21.192
♪ Hush, hush,
somebody's callin' my name ♪

14:21.236 --> 14:25.280
♪ Oh my Lord, oh my Lord,
what should I do? ♪

14:28.827 --> 14:30.159
(Bill sighs)

14:31.329 --> 14:34.163
Yes, this is Anissa's
very pink bedroom.

14:36.918 --> 14:40.128
At the time
that we painted this,
pink was the thing.

14:40.171 --> 14:42.130
(purring)

14:42.173 --> 14:45.466
Anissa's his person.
Tiger is Anissa's cat.

14:45.510 --> 14:48.595
After Anissa left...

14:48.638 --> 14:50.638
he would come up here
and he'd spend a lot of time

14:50.682 --> 14:52.140
just walking around,
nosing around,

14:52.183 --> 14:53.474
looking for Anissa.

14:55.061 --> 14:57.312
You know, nobody uses...

14:58.356 --> 15:00.773
the bed while she's gone.

15:00.817 --> 15:03.568
I don't know,
maybe the cat does, but...

15:03.612 --> 15:06.446
I guess it just made more sense
to take everything apart

15:06.489 --> 15:09.741
and wash it
and when she comes home,

15:09.784 --> 15:11.743
it's all clean
and ready to go.

15:12.787 --> 15:14.871
It's just a matter of when.

15:17.542 --> 15:20.668
She would come
in here to practice choir.

15:20.712 --> 15:24.130
She did projects
that she would have to FaceTime

15:24.174 --> 15:26.299
with two or three
different kids

15:26.343 --> 15:28.801
from this flight academy class
she was in.

15:28.845 --> 15:30.845
'Cause I'd pop in
on a regular basis.

15:30.889 --> 15:32.639
I'd just you know,
"What are you doing?"

15:32.682 --> 15:37.477
I see a face on the iPad.
"Okay, who are you talking to?"

15:37.520 --> 15:39.604
You know, "What are
you guys working on?"

15:40.982 --> 15:43.232
And then you know, most days...

15:45.070 --> 15:48.029
you know, 7:30, "Anissa,
you're done with your iPad.

15:48.073 --> 15:51.366
Shut it down,
come downstairs,
be with your family."

15:53.578 --> 15:54.786
And she never argued.

15:56.706 --> 16:01.125
People have asked me if I saw
any signs in my daughter
and this and that.

16:01.169 --> 16:04.504
And I'm just like,
"No. I knew what
she was doing in here.

16:04.547 --> 16:08.925
Because when she wasn't doing
her choir practice,
that door was open."

16:10.804 --> 16:12.345
You know, all of the kids--

16:12.389 --> 16:14.681
not just Anissa,
all of them--
they know...

16:14.724 --> 16:18.726
there's no closed doors
in this house unless you're...

16:18.770 --> 16:20.937
fresh out of the shower
or getting ready for bed.

16:22.315 --> 16:23.398
So...

16:24.859 --> 16:27.068
for people to say...

16:28.113 --> 16:29.779
I wasn't involved...

16:31.908 --> 16:36.577
Apart from sitting
in the corner and watching
every move she makes,

16:36.621 --> 16:38.579
I don't know how much
more involved I could've been.

16:38.623 --> 16:42.125
♪ ♪

16:42.168 --> 16:43.960
My focus is Anissa...

16:44.921 --> 16:46.003
not Slenderman.

17:01.438 --> 17:04.939
♪ ♪

17:30.759 --> 17:34.177
(cameras clicking)
(chains clinking)

17:41.853 --> 17:43.394
Forensics man on video:
<i> And what is your name?</i>

17:43.438 --> 17:46.147
Anissa Weier.
Anissa, okay.

17:46.191 --> 17:48.566
(camera clicking)

17:48.610 --> 17:50.067
Okay, Just kind of...

17:50.111 --> 17:52.153
give me a look.
Give me a look.

17:53.698 --> 17:55.823
♪ ♪

18:05.126 --> 18:06.334
(man whispers)
Morgan.

18:08.963 --> 18:10.671
How you doing?
Morgan:
Fine.

18:10.715 --> 18:11.756
Man:
Come on up.

18:11.800 --> 18:13.841
<i> (forensics man speaking</i>
<i> on video)</i>

18:15.053 --> 18:17.720
(Morgan speaks)
Morgan, all right.

18:32.403 --> 18:35.071
(people whispering)

18:41.371 --> 18:42.870
<i>(Morgan speaks</i>
<i>on video)</i>

18:44.624 --> 18:47.250
(Casey speaking)

