(Tiger meows)

55:48.471 --> 55:51.346
♪ ♪

55:55.019 --> 55:57.603
(murmuring)

56:05.529 --> 56:07.821
<i> (chains clinking)</i>

56:09.450 --> 56:12.117
(cameras clicking)

56:27.718 --> 56:29.718
Maggie:
<i> I don't know where</i>

56:29.762 --> 56:33.263
<i>the whole Slenderman thing...</i>

56:33.307 --> 56:36.642
<i> started because</i>
<i> Anissa never talked about</i>
<i> anything like that.</i>

56:36.685 --> 56:40.354
<i> Nobody ever talked</i>
<i> about Slenderman.</i>

56:40.397 --> 56:44.191
Unless she was, like,
constantly Internet surfing,

56:44.235 --> 56:47.903
she never really showed me
anything that was bad...

56:49.281 --> 56:52.157
or anything scary.

56:52.201 --> 56:55.619
She-- she is
easily frightened, though.

56:55.663 --> 56:58.622
(woman coughs)
(camera clicking)

56:58.666 --> 57:03.293
Maybe she did it
because she wanted
to be noticed.

57:03.337 --> 57:06.672
Because, honestly,
at her school

57:06.715 --> 57:09.967
I didn't know that
she didn't have many friends.

57:10.010 --> 57:13.804
She told me
that she had lots of friends,
lots of guys liked her,

57:13.848 --> 57:16.473
and a bunch of--
and she was accepted,

57:16.517 --> 57:18.934
and she was having
a great time at school.

57:18.978 --> 57:23.063
<i> But... she was</i>
<i> constantly picked on,</i>

57:23.107 --> 57:27.901
and she never really fit in.
She was a follower.

57:29.947 --> 57:31.572
Bailiff:
All rise.

57:34.201 --> 57:35.868
Bohren:
Okay, thank you.
Please be seated.

57:37.288 --> 57:40.414
Maggie:
<i> I think some kids</i>
<i> are just...</i>

57:41.876 --> 57:43.417
big believers.

57:43.460 --> 57:46.753
They can't help but believe
everything they hear.

57:50.259 --> 57:53.135
(rustles)

57:53.179 --> 57:55.012
Officer: Do you swear
to tell the truth,
the whole truth,

57:55.055 --> 57:56.555
and nothing but the truth,
so help you God?

57:56.599 --> 57:58.765
Yes, I do.
Attorney:
In this case

57:58.809 --> 58:02.561
were you assigned
to interview the victim,
Payton Leutner?

58:02.605 --> 58:04.021
Yes, I was.

58:04.064 --> 58:07.399
Attorney:
At some point, your discussion
got into the area

58:07.443 --> 58:10.319
of a birthday party
that was planned for Morgan?

58:10.362 --> 58:12.529
Payton said that
the birthday party

58:12.573 --> 58:14.740
had been planned
for several weeks,

58:14.783 --> 58:17.242
and it was for May 30th,

58:17.286 --> 58:20.579
and that they had planned
to go do Skateland

58:20.623 --> 58:22.581
and sleep over
at Morgan's house.

58:24.460 --> 58:25.959
Angie:
<i> They were being</i>
<i> normal little girls.</i>

58:26.003 --> 58:27.502
<i> They were running</i>
<i> up and down the stairs,</i>

58:27.546 --> 58:29.588
<i> holding hands</i>
<i> and giggling.</i>

58:32.426 --> 58:33.467
<i> There was no...</i>

58:34.470 --> 58:37.930
indication that anything
was-- was off

58:37.973 --> 58:39.848
or that we had anything to--

58:42.394 --> 58:44.436
to be worried about.

58:44.480 --> 58:47.522
After Skateland,
they came back to Morgan's house

58:47.566 --> 58:50.108
and they went
into the basement.

59:25.437 --> 59:27.562
(speaks matter-of-factly)

59:37.491 --> 59:39.032
And we-- we woke up
in the morning,

59:39.076 --> 59:43.578
and we had donuts
and strawberries
for breakfast,

59:43.622 --> 59:45.539
and everything
was very normal.

59:45.582 --> 59:47.499
The girls were laughing and...

59:48.419 --> 59:49.876
having a good time.

59:52.047 --> 59:54.881
And they asked
if they could go
to the park,

59:54.925 --> 59:56.842
and I didn't think
anything of it.

59:56.885 --> 59:58.844
I said, "Yeah, of course
you can go to the park."

59:58.887 --> 1:00:01.430
And, you know,
Morgan said goodbye

1:00:01.473 --> 1:00:03.056
and told me
she loved me.

1:00:03.100 --> 1:00:06.184
♪ ♪
(breathes shakily)

